data.title: Fred Below Jr. (1926-1988) – Find a Grave...
data.meta_description: Fred Below Jr. was born 16 September 1926 in Chicago, son of Fred Below Sr. and Dorothy Carter.  He was  an American blues drummer who worked with Little Walter and Chess Records in the 1950s. According to Tony Russell, Below was a creator of much of the rhythmic structure of Chicago blues, especially its backbeat. He...
